# Step 4 — Signed FA Contracts

Players who have already signed are listed here with their actual new AAV ($M).
**To update:** add rows as players sign. All other FAs remain as "Unsigned"
and get a model-predicted salary only.

```{r signed-contracts}
fa_signed <- tribble(
  ~Player,              ~Actual_New_AAV,
  "Trae Young",                   53.2,
  "Austin Reaves",                46.2,
  "Ayo Dosunmu",                  22.4,
  "Coby White",                   24.7,
  "Collin Gillespie",             12.0,
  "Mark Williams",                12.7,
  "Jordan Goodwin",                6.3,
  "Jose Alvarado",                 4.9,
  "Al Horford",                    7.0,
  "Mohamed Diawara",               2.5
) %>%
  mutate(Player = clean_name(Player))

# Attach signed status to the full FA list
fa_all <- fa_all %>%
  left_join(fa_signed, by = "Player") %>%
  mutate(Status = ifelse(is.na(Actual_New_AAV), "Unsigned", "Signed"))

cat(sprintf("Signed:   %d\n", sum(fa_all$Status == "Signed")))
cat(sprintf("Unsigned: %d\n", sum(fa_all$Status == "Unsigned")))
```

