# Step 7 — Split: Under Contract vs Free Agents

- **`df_model`** — players with a known `r SALARY_COL` salary. Used to train the model.
- **`fa_df`** — all 2026 FAs whose 2025-26 stats are available.

```{r split}
df_model <- combined_df %>%
  filter(!is.na(salary_clean)) %>%
  drop_na(all_of(FEATURES))

fa_df <- fa_all %>%
  inner_join(combined_df, by = "Player") %>%
  drop_na(all_of(FEATURES))

cat(sprintf("Under contract (training set):   %d players\n", nrow(df_model)))
cat(sprintf("FAs matched to stats — signed:   %d\n", sum(fa_df$Status == "Signed")))
cat(sprintf("FAs matched to stats — unsigned: %d\n", sum(fa_df$Status == "Unsigned")))
```

