# Step 8 — Standardise Features

Every feature is z-score standardised (subtract mean, divide by SD). Parameters
are computed from the training set only and reapplied to the FA set in Step 10.

```{r standardise}
X_train <- df_model %>% select(all_of(FEATURES))
X_means <- colMeans(X_train)
X_sds   <- apply(X_train, 2, sd)

X_scaled <- scale_features(df_model)
y_train  <- df_model$salary_clean

train_data           <- as.data.frame(X_scaled)
colnames(train_data) <- FEATURES
train_data$salary    <- y_train
```

```{r feature-dist, echo=FALSE, fig.height=4, fig.cap="After standardisation every feature should be centered near 0."}
as.data.frame(X_scaled) %>%
  setNames(FEATURES) %>%
  pivot_longer(everything(), names_to = "Feature", values_to = "z") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = z, fill = Feature)) +
  geom_density(alpha = 0.4, show.legend = FALSE) +
  facet_wrap(~ Feature, scales = "free_y", ncol = 5) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Standardised feature distributions", x = "z-score", y = NULL)
```

