# Step 9 — Bayesian Linear Regression

Each feature gets a weight (`beta`). Predicted salary = weighted sum of
standardised stats + intercept.

| Parameter | Prior | Meaning |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| `beta` | Normal(0, 1) | No strong belief any one stat dominates |
| `intercept` | Normal(0, 5) | Average salary can be anywhere in a wide range |
| `sigma` | Exponential(1) | Predictions are not perfect |

```{r fit-model, results='hide', cache=TRUE}
# Backtick-wrap feature names to handle % and spaces in column names.
# Stan internally mangles these (e.g. "3P%" -> "3P.") so feature_pars
# uses grep() on dimnames() rather than referencing FEATURES directly.
model_formula <- as.formula(
  paste("salary ~", paste(paste0("`", FEATURES, "`"), collapse = " + "))
)

bayes_model <- stan_glm(
  formula         = model_formula,
  data            = train_data,
  family          = gaussian(),
  prior           = normal(location = 0, scale = 1, autoscale = FALSE),
  prior_intercept = normal(location = 0, scale = 5, autoscale = FALSE),
  prior_aux       = exponential(rate = 1, autoscale = FALSE),
  chains          = CHAINS,
  iter            = ITER,
  warmup          = WARMUP,
  seed            = SEED,
  refresh         = 0
)
```

```{r model-summary, echo=FALSE}
as.data.frame(summary(bayes_model)) %>%
  tibble::rownames_to_column("Parameter") %>%
  filter(Parameter != "log-posterior") %>%
  mutate(across(where(is.numeric), ~ round(., 3))) %>%
  kable(caption = "Posterior summary — mean, SD, and credible intervals") %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped","hover","condensed"), full_width = FALSE)
```

```{r coef-plot, echo=FALSE, fig.height=5, fig.cap="Bars that don't cross zero have the strongest relationship to salary."}
posterior_draws <- as.array(bayes_model)
feature_pars    <- grep("Intercept|sigma",
                        dimnames(posterior_draws)$parameters,
                        invert = TRUE, value = TRUE)

mcmc_intervals(posterior_draws, pars = feature_pars, prob = 0.80, prob_outer = 0.95) +
  labs(title = "Feature coefficients (80% and 95% credible intervals)",
       x     = "Effect on predicted salary ($M, standardised features)")
```

```{r trace-plot, echo=FALSE, fig.height=6, fig.cap="Fuzzy caterpillars = good mixing. Trends or drifts = model needs more iterations."}
posterior_draws <- as.array(bayes_model)
feature_pars    <- grep("Intercept|sigma",
                        dimnames(posterior_draws)$parameters,
                        invert = TRUE, value = TRUE)

mcmc_trace(posterior_draws,
           pars = c("(Intercept)", feature_pars[1:4], "sigma")) +
  labs(title = "MCMC trace plots — intercept, first 4 features, sigma")
```

